<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>TSI 01-03-05 - Misapplication Of Steer Axle Shock Absorbers In 3000 FE and 3000 RE Bus Models</stitle>
    <tsi id="tsi010305" tsitype="truck">
        <tsinumber>01-03-05</tsinumber>
        <tsidate>September, 2001</tsidate>
        <subjectfile>SPRINGS</subjectfile>
        <subjectgroup>
            <subject>Misapplication Of Steer Axle Shock Absorbers In 3000 FE and 3000 RE Bus Models</subject>
        </subjectgroup>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <truckmodelgroup/>

                <truckmodel>3000</truckmodel>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>FE and RE bus steering axle shock absorbers can be misapplied. The FE and RE shock absorbers are
                    physically similar, and either shock will fit in either application. The weight requirements of FE
                    and RE require different shock damping and the use of an incorrect shock absorber may result in poor
                    ride quality. The shock absorbers for 3000 FE/RE models are identified with an "FE" or "RE"
                    designator after the part number
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0103051">(Figure 1)</hotlnk>.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <caution>
                        <para>Steer axle shock absorber calibration is not the same for 3000 FE and 3000 RE chassis bus
                            applications, due to weight distribution requirements. Use of incorrect parts may diminish
                            performance and cause premature wear out.
                        </para>
                    </caution>
                </specpara>
                <figure id="f0103051" figsize="pg-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G0103051.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="502px"
                             scalefitheight="352px" resolution="325"/>
                    <caption>Figure 1. Shock Absorber</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. PART NUMBER WITH RE OR FE MODEL DESIGNATOR</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
